bool ExpandedRoute::getRouteLandmarkDescription (  uint32  index,
uint32  i,
char *  buf,
uint32  maxLength
)  const
 

Creates a route landmark description for a ExpandedRouteItem.

For instance "After 15 km pass Landskrona".

Parameters:
index The index of the ExpandedRouteItem to get landmark description for.
i The landmark's index for the ExpandedRouteItem. Get valid landmark indexes from getNbrLandmarksForExpandedRouteItem().
buf Preallocated buffer which will be filled with the route landmark description.
maxLength The length of buf.
nbrBytesWritten The number of bytes written into buf.
Returns:
True If index is < getNbrExpandedRouteItems and i < getNbrLandmarksForExpandedRouteItem( index ) and the route landmark description did fit in the buffer, false otherwise.

void ExpandedRoute::setRouteDescriptionProperties (  StringTable::languageCode  lang,
bool  compassLangShort,
byte  maxTurnNumbers,
bool  printSignPostText,
StringTableUtility::distanceFormat  distFormat,
StringTableUtility::distanceUnit  distUnit,
bool  wapFormat,
const char *  nameSeparator = "/"
) 
 

Set the route description properties according to the specified parameters.

Parameters:
lang Language code of the route description.
compassLangShort If compass direction should be short.
maxTurnNumbers Maximum number of turns that should be printed out. Eg "turn left at the 9:th road". NB! Must be <= 9 for now as expansion on overview maps sets it to 10 to set it as invalid.
printSignPostText Set this to true if signpost texts should be printed out.
distFormat Distance format used when printing the distance.
wapFormat Set this to true if the text should be wap formatted. All text that displayed on a wap phone must be formatted (for instance swedish characters must be replaced with escape-codes and so on).
